          defense: 'Use WPA3 where hardware supports it — it replaces PSK with SAE (Simultaneous Authentication of Equals), resistant to offline dictionary attacks. For enterprise environments, use WPA2/3-Enterprise with 802.1X and per-user credentials — no shared key exists to steal. Disable legacy protocols (WEP, WPA). Deploy a wireless intrusion detection system to alert on rogue APs and deauth storms. On untrusted networks, use a VPN to encrypt all traffic regardless of the Wi-Fi layer.',
