          impact: 'Security+ is the most widely recognized entry-level security certification and is DoD 8570/8140 approved — required for many US government and contractor positions. It validates a baseline of security knowledge across domains rather than deep expertise in one area. Most employers treat it as a minimum threshold for junior security analyst and SOC roles.',
